title: Narrative

* This example shows how to customise the level indicator, which is shown when the `level` parameter limits the tree depth

* The `toc-level-indicator` procedure is overridden locally: instead of the default icon, nodes with hidden children show a superscript ''more'' marker

* With `level:"1"` only the first level is shown. [[aa]] and [[bb]] have children, so they get the marker. [[cc]] has none

{{example-overview}}

+
title: Description

TOC custom level indicator
+
title: Output

\procedure toc-level-indicator()
<%if [<level>compare:number:gt[0]]%>
	<%if [subfilter<tf.toc-filterString>] -[<tag>] +[limit[1]] %>
		<sup class="tc-tiny-gap-left">more</sup>
	<%endif%>
<%endif%>
\end

The `toc-level-indicator` procedure is overridden locally in this example.

<div class="tc-table-of-contents">
<<toc tag:"Contents" level:"1">>
</div>
